Review Summary: We paid them to pick us up and they were a no show when we finally got someone on the phone the hung up on us. They advertise a shuttle service Frisco shuttle who are very unreliable.

However, it sounded like the guests above us were moving furniture around and doing some serious stomping until about 3 am. I initially liked the hardwood floors when we entered our room- definitely cleaner than carpeting.

Hotel Name: Wingate by Wyndham Lake Charles Casino Area
Review Summary: First time staying at this hotel, found it to be what a travel would expect during a business trip. I was very pleased that my entire stay went off with out a problem.
We also were not impressed with the powdered scrambled eggs in the breakfast buffet. I found a spider in the bed when I rolled back the sheets to go to bed.

My wife and I decided to try it because of the previous three reviews, they were new to Expedia and it was a great price for room. We like to get away on weekends a few times a month and on weekends when our inconsiderate neighbors play loud music.

When I walked in the the lobby to check in the manager and the general manager greeted me with kindness and it felt really good. Thank you for sharing your experience with us and we hope we get the privilege to serve you again soon.
Bad: The bed wasn't comfortable at all. Good: The room was very very clean.
We spent one night here (in the suite) and wished we had the time to stay longer. Warning - the IPA at Prodigal Sons Brewing company sneaks up on you...

The rooms were nice and location was fantastic but its a shame the desk staff doesn't have a clue, I will not be returning to this chain and also will push my friends and family to avoid it as well.   After waiting at the counter for over 20 minutes while the attendant the manager finally came over and gave us keys and assured it is fine the rate is the same and enjoy the stay.

Unfortunately, the Wyndham Garden Elk Grove Village has been one of the worst examples of bad customer service I have ever encountered. I try to be fair and objective in my TripAdvisor reviews, because I take others' reviews seriously when booking a hotel.

The best part of all for me was the fact that they have real hair dryers in the room, not just one that blows barely above a whisper! The room was exceptionally spacious and comfortable, including a wet bar area and done in soothing colors of browns and teals.

The shuttle driver told us that the hotel was recently under new management and a lot of items that were left by the former management is now getting done.   Other than being told on hotels.com that breakfast was included in our cost, but it wasn't, the stay was wonderful.

Hotel Name: Wyndham Garden San Jose Silicon Valley
Review Summary: I have to say that I was scare at first that my reservation was going to be denied, because there was many people with that problem before me. But when it was my turn, everything went well and actually because the hotel was full, they gave a better room for the same price.

Category: Hotels and motels,Hotel and motel reservations,Wedding supplies, services, chapels, facilities, etc.,Hotel,Hotels,Lodging
Review Summary: room seemed OK at first, but curtains were not hung properly, (just dangling from rod) I had a large beetle in my bed, the chair in room was covered in red pen/marker, and seriously, there... elevator flooring was broken/peeling/popping up, and there was literally duct tape on walls holding parts together....

Hotel Name: Wyndham Houston - Medical Center Hotel and Suites

Review Summary: Hotel did a great job with shuttle service for KC Chiefs fan to playoff game in Houston. We had a very restful night and plan on staying again next month.

The location is perfect for exploring Boston and for anywhere a little further, a driving service is offered. The rate is expensive, but we enjoyed the high-level of service with multiple tidy services offered each day.
Nothing fancy, but clean, well maintained rooms and cabins, good food, prompt service. The staff is amazing, and they make your feel welcome, in true Alaskan fashion.

Excellent security staff -- Cheerfully and efficiently retrieved my forgotten keyboard, assured me it was safe, and FedExed it to me no charge. Desk staff are meh, but bartenders, concierge and gorgeous door men are all great, Super helpful and friendly

I travel often for business and I was absolutely blown away by the wonderful customer service I received at this particular location. More  Excellent accommodations, excellent staff, super super breakfast in the morning, with everything you can imagine.

Category: Hotels,Boutique Hotels,Resort,Hotels and motels,Lodging,Hotels Motels,Luxury Hotels,Motels,Hotel
Review Summary: They have friendly and knowledgable staff and overall it was the best experience I have had of a hotel. Room was very clean, comfortable beds, and very good continental breakfasts delivered to our rooms.
